value.def: A ramp is a sloping surface between two places that are at different levels.
An entrance ramp is a road which cars use to drive onto a major road, and an exit ramp is a road which cars use to drive off a major road.
value.tran: （车辆进出主路时用的）匝道，坡道

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, use 英国英语用 slip road
